Spanish Stocks: Tecnicas Reunidas, Sacyr, Clinica Baviera Move

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-02-14T17:02:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/spanish-stocks-acs-tecnicas-reunidas-ohl-fluidra-shares-move.html
Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  fell for a
third day in four, losing 28.9, or 0.3 percent, to 10,774.7 at
the 5:30 p.m. close in Madrid. The Madrid Stock Exchange General
Index also dropped 0.3 percent today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.    Clinica Baviera SA  (CBAV SM) jumped 2.5 percent to 8.20
euros, the highest price since September. The Spanish company
was raised to “buy” from “neutral” at UBS AG.  Fluidra SA (FDR SM) climbed for the first day in three,
adding 2.9 percent to 2.69 euros. The maker of swimming pools
agreed to buy Aquatron Inc., Aqua Products Inc. and assets of
Aquatron Robotic Systems Ltd. for an initial $44 million.    Obrascon Huarte Lain SA  (OHL SM) advanced for the sixth
time in seven days, gaining 1.6 percent to 24.19 euros. The
Spanish construction company’s Brazilian unit said Brazil’s
state development bank, known as BNDES, approved a loan of 331.3
million reais ($199 million) to the company.  Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV SM) climbed 5.2 percent to 8.10
euros, the stock’s fourth straight gain. The Spanish builder and
the group of companies in charge of expanding the Panama Canal
finished 10 percent of the construction works, to ensure the
project remains on schedule, El Economista reported, citing
Antonio Zafaroni, chief executive officer of the group.    Tecnicas Reunidas SA  (TRE SM) dropped for a fourth day in
five, losing 2.4 percent to 43.30 euros. The Spanish engineering
company was cut to “equal weight” from “overweight” at
Morgan Stanley.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in  Madrid  at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
